26#pragma once
27
28#include "NetworkCacheStorage.h"
29#include <WebCore/DOMCacheEngine.h>
30#include <wtf/Vector.h>
31#include <wtf/text/WTFString.h>
32
33namespace WebCore {
34struct RetrieveRecordsOptions;
35}
36
37namespace WebKit {
38
39namespace CacheStorage {
40
41class Caches;
42
43struct RecordInformation {
44 NetworkCache::Key key;
45 double insertionTime { 0 };
46
47 uint64_t identifier { 0 };
48 uint64_t updateResponseCounter { 0 };
49
50 uint64_t size { 0 };
51
52 URL url;
53 bool hasVaryStar { false };
54 HashMap<String, String> varyHeaders;
55};
56
57class AsynchronousPutTaskCounter;
58class ReadRecordTaskCounter;
59
60class Cache {
61public:
62 enum class State { Uninitialized, Opening, Open };
63 Cache(Caches&, uint64_t identifier, State, String&& name, String&& uniqueName);
64
65 bool isOpened() const { return m_state == State::Open; }
66 void open(WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&&);
67
68 uint64_t identifier() const { return m_identifier; }
69 const String& name() const { return m_name; }
70 const String& uniqueName() const { return m_uniqueName; }
71 bool isActive() const { return m_state != State::Uninitialized; }
72
73 void retrieveRecords(const WebCore::RetrieveRecordsOptions&, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::RecordsCallback&&);
74 WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CacheInfo info() const { return { m_identifier, m_name }; }
75
76 void put(Vector<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record>&&, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::RecordIdentifiersCallback&&);
77 void remove(WebCore::ResourceRequest&&, WebCore::CacheQueryOptions&&, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::RecordIdentifiersCallback&&);
78
79 Vector<NetworkCache::Key> keys() const;
80
81 void dispose();
82 void clearMemoryRepresentation();
83
84 static std::optional<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record> decode(const NetworkCache::Storage::Record&);
85 static NetworkCache::Storage::Record encode(const RecordInformation&, const WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record&);
86
87 struct DecodedRecord {
88 DecodedRecord(double insertionTime, uint64_t size, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record&& record)
89 : insertionTime(insertionTime)
90 , size(size)
91 , record(WTFMove(record))
92 { }
93
94 double insertionTime { 0 };
95 uint64_t size { 0 };
96 WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record record;
97 };
98 static std::optional<DecodedRecord> decodeRecordHeader(const NetworkCache::Storage::Record&);
99
100 bool hasPendingOpeningCallbacks() const { return !m_pendingOpeningCallbacks.isEmpty(); }
101
102private:
103 Vector<RecordInformation>* recordsFromURL(const URL&);
104 const Vector<RecordInformation>* recordsFromURL(const URL&) const;
105 RecordInformation& addRecord(Vector<RecordInformation>*, const WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record&);
106
107 void storeRecords(Vector<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record>&&, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::RecordIdentifiersCallback&&);
108
109 RecordInformation toRecordInformation(const WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record&);
110
111 void finishOpening(WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&&, std::optional<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Error>&&);
112 void retrieveRecord(const RecordInformation&, Ref<ReadRecordTaskCounter>&&);
113
114 void readRecordsList(WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&&);
115 void writeRecordToDisk(const RecordInformation&, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record&&, Ref<AsynchronousPutTaskCounter>&&, uint64_t previousRecordSize);
116 void updateRecordToDisk(RecordInformation&, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record&&, Ref<AsynchronousPutTaskCounter>&&);
117 void removeRecordFromDisk(const RecordInformation&);
118 void readRecordFromDisk(const RecordInformation&, WTF::Function<void(Expected<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Error>&&)>&&);
119 void removeFromRecordList(const Vector<uint64_t>&);
120
121 Caches& m_caches;
122 State m_state;
123 uint64_t m_identifier { 0 };
124 String m_name;
125 String m_uniqueName;
126 HashMap<String, Vector<RecordInformation>> m_records;
127 uint64_t m_nextRecordIdentifier { 0 };
128 Vector<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback> m_pendingOpeningCallbacks;
129};
130
131} // namespace CacheStorage
132
133} // namespace WebKit
